# 詞: 銀包

1. 我個銀包忘咗喺屋企，而家身無分文。 (I left my wallet at home, so I have no money with me right now.)
2. 呢個真皮銀包好靚，但價錢真係唔平。 (This leather wallet is very nice, but the price is really not cheap.)
3. 佢成日話要慳錢，但個銀包總係空空如也。 (He always says he wants to save money, but his wallet is always empty.)
4. 唔好亂咁花錢，小心個銀包頂唔順。 (Don't spend money recklessly, or your wallet won't be able to handle it.)
5. 我喺街邊撿到一個銀包，裡面仲有幾張銀行咭。 (I found a wallet on the street, and there were still several bank cards inside.)
6. 送佢一個新銀包做生日禮物，佢好開心。 (I gave him a new wallet as a birthday gift, and he was very happy.)
7. 個銀包太舊咗，我想換個新嘅。 (This wallet is too old; I want to get a new one.)
8. 佢個銀包入面塞滿咗收據同舊車票。 (His wallet is stuffed with receipts and old train tickets.)
9. 小心個銀包，唔好畀扒手偷咗去。 (Be careful with your wallet; don't let a pickpocket steal it.)
10. 我個銀包壞咗，個拉鏈都拉唔上。 (My wallet is broken; the zipper won't even close.) [end of text]


